The paper discusses collaborative machine learning and related techniques, which are primarily related to the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The attacks developed in the paper involve inference and privacy concerns, which are also relevant to the field of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning for tasks such as gender classification in photos (cs.CV) and the limitations and defenses against attacks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms to infer properties of training data, which is related to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
